%h1= @page_title = "About Opening Times"

%p Opening Times provides opening times information for facilities such as shops, restaurants, libraries in the UK.

%h2 Source Code

%p The source code and data are both available under an open license.

%ul
  %li
    = link_to 'Opening Times source code', 'http://github.com/aubergene/Opening-Times'
    (Ruby on Rails)


%h2 Open Data

%p
  The Opening Times data are made available under the Open Database License:
  = link_to('http://opendatacommons.org/licenses/odbl/1.0/','http://opendatacommons.org/licenses/odbl/1.0/') + '.'
  Any rights in individual contents of the database are licensed under the Database Contents License:
  = link_to('http://opendatacommons.org/licenses/dbcl/1.0/','http://opendatacommons.org/licenses/dbcl/1.0/') + '.'

%p
  The files are compressed, you can use
  = link_to('7zip', 'http://www.7-zip.org/')
  to decompress.

%ul
  - ["sql","csv","xml"].each do |ext|
    - size = File.size("#{RAILS_ROOT}/public/export/facilities.#{ext}.gz") rescue "missing file"
    %li= link_to(ext, "/export/facilities.#{ext}.gz") + " - #{number_to_human_size(size)}"

